"Fichefet T., Poncin C., Goosse H., Huybrechts P., Janssens I., Le Treut H.","Implications of changes in freshwater flux from the Greenland ice sheet for the climate of the 21st century",2003,"Geophysical Research Letters","30","17",,"CLM 8","1 - 8-4",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0346216924&partnerID=40&md5=f23d64b6dff666259d3f67959ece27c5","Inst. d'Astron./Geophys. Georges, Universite Catholique de Louvain, Louvain-la-Neuve B-1348, Belgium; Departement Geografie, Vrije Universiteit Brussel, Brussels B-1050, Belgium; Alfred-Wegener-Inst. f. Polar, Bremerhaven, Germany; Lab. de Meteorol. Dynamique du CNRS, Ecole Normale Supérieure, Paris Cedex 05 F-75231, France","Fichefet, T., Inst. d'Astron./Geophys. Georges, Universite Catholique de Louvain, Louvain-la-Neuve B-1348, Belgium; Poncin, C., Inst. d'Astron./Geophys. Georges, Universite Catholique de Louvain, Louvain-la-Neuve B-1348, Belgium; Goosse, H., Inst. d'Astron./Geophys. Georges, Universite Catholique de Louvain, Louvain-la-Neuve B-1348, Belgium; Huybrechts, P., Departement Geografie, Vrije Universiteit Brussel, Brussels B-1050, Belgium, Alfred-Wegener-Inst. f. Polar, Bremerhaven, Germany; Janssens, I., Departement Geografie, Vrije Universiteit Brussel, Brussels B-1050, Belgium; Le Treut, H., Lab. de Meteorol. Dynamique du CNRS, Ecole Normale Supérieure, Paris Cedex 05 F-75231, France","Two simulations of the 21st century climate have been carried out using, on the one hand, a coarse resolution climate general circulation model and, on the other hand, the same model coupled to a comprehensive model of the Greenland ice sheet. Both simulations display a gradual global warming up to 2080. In the experiment that includes an interactive ice sheet component, a strong and abrupt weakening of the North Atlantic thermohaline circulation occurs at the end of the 21st century. This feature is triggered by an enhanced freshwater input arising mainly from a partial melting of the Greenland ice sheet. As a consequence of the circulation decline, a marked cooling takes place over eastern Greenland and the northern North Atlantic. This result underlines the potential role of the Greenland ice sheet in the evolution of climate over the 21st century.",,"Global warming; Ice; Ice sheets; Geophysics; atmosphere-ice-ocean system; climate change; freshwater input; ice sheet; melting; numerical model; thermohaline circulation",,,,,,"Dickson, R.R., Meincke, J., Malmberg, S.-A., Lee, A.J., The ""Great Salinity Anomaly"" in the northern North Atlantic, 1968-1982 (1988) Progr. Oceanogr., 20, pp. 103-151; Ganopolski, A., Rahmstorf, S., Rapid changes of glacial climate simulated in a coupled climate model (2001) Nature, 409, pp. 153-158; Goosse, H., Fichefet, T., Importance of ice-ocean interactions for the global ocean circulation: A model study (1999) J. Geophys. Res., 104, pp. 23337-23355; Gordon, A.L., Interocean exchange of thermocline water (1986) J. Geophys. Res., 91, pp. 5037-5046; Grenier, H., Le Treut, H., Fichefet, T., Ocean-atmosphere interactions and climate drift in a coupled general circulation model (2000) Clim. Dyn., 16, pp. 701-717; Huybrechts, P., de Wolde, J., The dynamic response of the Greenland and Antarctic ice sheets to multiple-century climatic warming (1999) J. Clim., 12, pp. 2169-2188; Huybrechts, P., Janssens, I., Poncin, C., Fichefet, T., The response of the Greenland ice sheet to climate changes in the 21st century by interactive coupling of an AOGCM with a thermomechanical ice sheet model (2002) Ann. Glaciol., 35, pp. 409-415; (2001) Climate Change 2001: The Scientific Basis. Contribution of Working Group I to the Third Assessment Report of the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change, , IPCC, edited by J. T. Houghton, Y. Ding, D. J. Griggs, M. Noguer, P. J. Van der Linden, X. Dai, K. Maskell, and C. A. Johnson, Cambridge Univ. Press, Cambridge, U.K., 881 pp; Janssens, I., Huybrechts, P., The treatment of meltwater retention in mass-balance parameterizations of the Greenland ice sheet (2000) Ann. Glaciol., 31, pp. 133-140; Mitchell, J.F.B., Davis, R.A., Ingram, W.J., Senior, C.A., On surface temperature, greenhouse gases, and aerosols: Models and observations (1995) J. Clim., 8, pp. 2364-2386; Rahmstorf, S., Bifurcations of the Atlantic thermohaline circulation in response to changes in the hydrological cycle (1995) Nature, 378, pp. 145-149; Rahmstorf, S., Shifting seas in the greenhouse? (1999) Nature, 399, pp. 523-524; Schaeffer, M., Selten, F.M., Goosse, H., Opsteegh, J.D., Limited predictability of regional climate change in IPCC SRES scenarios (2002) Geophys. Res. Lett., 29 (16). , doi:10.1029/2002GL015254; Schmittner, A., Yoshimori, M., Weaver, A.J., Instability of glacial climate in a model of the ocean-atmosphere-cryosphere system (2002) Science, 295, pp. 1489-1493; Stommel, H., Thermohaline convection with two stables regimes of flow (1961) Tellus, 13, pp. 225-230; Wang, Z., Mysak, L., Ice sheet-thermohaline circulation interactions in a climate model of intermediate complexity (2001) J. Oceanogr., 57, pp. 481-494","Fichefet, T.; Inst. d'Astron./Geophys. Georges, Universite Catholique de Louvain, Louvain-la-Neuve B-1348, Belgium; email: fichefet@astr.ucl.ac.be",,,,,,,,00948276,,GPRLA,,"English","Geophys. Res. Lett.",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-0346216924
